title: Iranian police say death of Mahsa Amini 'unfortunate' as protestors take to the streets
description: Iranian police called the death of Mahsa Amini an "unfortunate incident" and denied that she was harmed physically in custody, semi-official news agency Fars News said on Monday.

title: World leaders gather 'at time of great peril' at UN
description: It took a Queen to shake up this year's high-level week at the United Nations General Assembly -- an annual whirlwind shindig known as UNGA that will begin on Tuesday.

title: Paris subway station renamed 'Elizabeth II' for day of Queen's funeral
description: The Paris transportation network RATP announced it has changed the name of one of its stations to honor Queen Elizabeth II on the day of her funeral.

title: Why the current oil boom for Arab states may be their last
description: The oil boom brought about by the Ukraine war has made energy-rich Middle Eastern countries extraordinarily wealthy once again. But experts warn that it may be the last such upswing.

title: Volkswagen targets 75 billion euro valuation in landmark Porsche IPO
description: Volkswagen is targeting a valuation of up to 75 billion euros ($75.1 billion) for luxury sportscar maker Porsche, it said on Sunday, in what will be Germany's second-largest initial public offering (IPO) in history.

title: 1 in 5 of China's urban youth are unemployed. That's a huge headache for Xi Jinping
description: The future looked promising for Cherry in May last year, when she secured a prestigious internship at a major software firm, while still studying at a university in Wuhan. The company told her that she could start working for them full time, once she graduates.
